summary: SummaryThe MAC Studio Fix Powder Plus Foundation is a one-step, two-in-one refillable foundation and setting powder in a blur-matte finish with 24-hour oil control in 67 shades for all.
details: DetailsBenefits24 hours of oil/shine control12 hours of stay-true colour/fade-resistance and non-streaking/non-caking/non-settling coverageSilky talc-free textureImmediately reduces appearance of pores96% said it leaves skin feeling comfortable all day*94% said it smooths and blurs the look of skin blemishes**Consumer testing on 165 women after one week of product use.FeaturesWaterproofSweat- and humidity-resistantPhoto-friendly with no grey castFor all skin types; does not cause acneKey IngredientsRoseSugar kelpRed algae extractsItem 2636012How To UseApply this powder foundation to prepped skin.For lighter coverage, use a fluffy brush like the 168S Brush.To build coverage, apply with the included sponge applicator or a 170S Brush. Store sponge in the compartment underneath the powder instead of on top of the powder.For additional coverage and wear, buff Studio Fix Fluid SPF 15 onto skin using the 159S Brush before applying the powder.|To use as a setting powder, apply with the 240S Brush to your T-zone area and the 187S Brush all over the face.Finish your application with a light spritz of Fix+ to give skin a fresh appearance.IngredientsSynthetic Fluorphlogopite, Magnesium Potassium Fluorosilicate, Boron Nitride, Aluminum Starch Octenylsuccinate, Aluminum Hydroxide, Octyldodecyl Stearoyl Stearate, Hydrogenated Vegetable Oil, Silica, Dimethicone, Illite, Zinc Stearate, Dicalcium Phosphate, Pentaerythrityl Tetraisostearate, Silybum Marianum Seed Oil, Nannochloropsis Oculata Extract, Alaria Esculenta Extract, Porphyra Umbilicalis Extract, Rosa Hybrid Flower Extract, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Caprylyl Glycol, Bisabolol, Ethylhexylglycerin, Kaolin, Mica, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Sorbitan Tristearate, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Tocopherol, [+/- Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491), Iron Oxides (CI 77492), Iron Oxides (CI 77499), Bismuth Oxychloride (CI 77163), Chromium Hydroxide Green (CI 77289), Chromium Oxide Greens (CI 77288), Ferric Ammonium Ferrocyanide (CI 77510), Ferric Ferrocyanide (CI 77510), Manganese Violet (CI 77742), Red 6 (CI 15850), Red 7 (CI 15850), Ultramarines (CI 77007), Blue 1 Lake (CI 42090), Red 7 Lake (CI 15850), Red 28 Lake (CI 45410), Red 30 Lake (CI 73360), Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140), Yellow 6 Lake (CI 15985)].Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: My go-to foundation !
reviews.comments: This is the best foundation I've ever used.  It goes on light but it covers beautifully, and I don't need to top it off with face powder. I love it.  One compact lasts me for months, so it's a great value, too!

reviews.headline: Irritating they changed the product quality
reviews.comments: Really disappointed they changed something that I wore for 20 years and was AMAZING to something not nearly as good of a product. I had to return to the store THREE times to find my proper shade. They didn't keep the numbers the same, they're all too warm, and it doesn't go on as well and shows in the lines more. PLEASE bring back the old style!!

reviews.headline: Warning: New Formula - Very Bad!
reviews.comments: I have been a loyal MAC customer for over 10 years. They recently changed this formula (which used to be great). It is horrible now and I must switch to another brand. Why change a good thing? MAC, you have made a big mistake and are going to lose many customers over this. Very disappointed!!!

reviews.headline: it is fragile.
reviews.comments: I put it in my bag and the worst part is it broke when I got home, no hard impact, no dropping on the floor, a waste of my money, I will not be buying again!

reviews.headline: I would buy this product again
reviews.comments: Love it

reviews.headline: I would buy this again.
reviews.comments: Really stays on all day. I am able to apply more for full coverage on areas where I want it. Super lightweight feel.

reviews.headline: Mixed Thoughts
reviews.comments: I have been using the original formula of this for years and have since purchased the new formula. While the product is still great (Aside from the color formulas completely changing and needing to be re-color matched) the product is not lasting as it previously would. It used to last 4-5 months and the new formula lasted me 6 weeks.

reviews.headline: Hate the reformulation
reviews.comments: I've used this for YEARS and loved it, but it's been reformulated and it's no longer any good. NW30 is now way more yellow and is no longer a match for my skin tone. In addition, it's not nearly as oil absorbent as the old version. Please bring back the old version!

reviews.headline: New Formula üëéüèª
reviews.comments: I have used this product for over 12 years, since I started wearing makeup. Unfortunately I will not be purchasing again. M.A.C. changed the formula and it is no where near similar to the old formula. It does not provide the same coverage, and the product runs out way faster than the previous formula. Very unfortunate..

reviews.headline: Product shrinkflation
reviews.comments: Ive been buying studio fix for years and this new line of it is a joke. It comes with barely any powder foundation. The old line would last me months and this new one is almost out after just one month. Shrinkflation to the maximum. So upsetting.

reviews.headline: Not the same
reviews.comments: They changed the line and the colors are way different. My biggest complaint is it lasts like 1 month. The other lasted me at least a couple. Super bummed, but ill be finding a different product.

reviews.headline: N5 is now NW20 see MAC's website
reviews.comments: I have been buying this item for approx 2 decades. I purchased some online in May and recently went to use it and knew the color wasn't N5, so I called MAC because I thought the company had packaged them incorrectly. MAC told me N5 is now NW20. They told me if you go to their website, it will tell you if you wore N5, your best shade match is now NW20. This isn't the only color that changed letters/numbers. ULTA on your website under this product please put it in bold letters that the letters/numbers of items has changed. FYI: the old item was 0.52 oz and now it's 0.42 oz. I love ULTA and I'm assuming they weren't notified of these changes.

reviews.headline: Love it!
reviews.comments: I don't wear makeup often. It goes on so smooth and covers well.

reviews.headline: I hate the change
reviews.comments: They really should've notified everyone to say that it is a new color scheme as well as new packaging. Not only that my compacts used to last me a couple months and this one barely lasts me a month and a half so I'm going through it way faster, which is weird because I'm not wearing it anymore than I ever have. If anything I've been trying to wear it less because I keep seeing how much of it goes away every time I use it. I have been using this Studio fix foundation plus powder for literally 20 years and for them to switch it up like this is so stupid. Really not a fan almost makes me want to change brands and that feels crazy.

reviews.headline: Old formula way better
reviews.comments: I was NC43 with old formula and I was matched with NC44 on the new formula and it was just way to dark definitely miss NC43 :(

reviews.headline: New formulation is trash
reviews.comments: New formulation is trash, the colors don't match and it doesn't look natural, I've been using this product for many years but now I'm looking for a different brand that works the way the old formulation did.

reviews.headline: Hate it!!
reviews.comments: My go to powder was the old formulation and now this new formulation sucks so bad! Im very upset that Mac would change such a great product! Will not buy!

reviews.headline: Don't trust MACs shade match recommendations for new version
reviews.comments: MAC's website states "If you wore NW10, your best shade match is still NW10 in the NEW Studio Fix Powder Plus Foundation."‚Äîwell, that was a lie. New shade is significantly darker and looks orange on me. Waste of money.

reviews.headline: Daily User!
reviews.comments: I love this powder foundation. I've been using it for several months now and it's become one of my faves. I'm very oily and this does a good job of keeping the oil at bay for most of the day. And the color match was perfect! Buildable coverage is also a plus!

reviews.headline: It's okay
reviews.comments: Great coverage. Doesn't feel like I have makeup on. But, the product is very powdery and therefore messy. I won't buy again.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I received this product for free from Topbox Marketing for testing and review purposes.MAC Studio Fix Powder Plus Foundation Review: A Classic for a Reason
MAC Studio Fix Powder Plus Foundation has long been a staple in many makeup bags, and for good reason. This one-step powder and foundation offers a convenient way to achieve a medium to full, matte coverage with minimal effort.
What I love:
 * Versatile Coverage: Whether you're looking for a light dusting to even out your skin tone or buildable coverage to conceal imperfections, Studio Fix can deliver. It adapts well to different application methods, from a fluffy brush for lighter coverage to the included sponge for a more full-on look.
 * Excellent Shade Range: MAC is renowned for its extensive shade range, and Studio Fix is no exception. With a wide variety of undertones and depths, it's highly likely you'll find a perfect match for your skin. This inclusivity is a major plus.
 * Long-Wearing Power: This powder truly lives up to its claims of being long-wearing. It stays put for hours, controlling shine and keeping your complexion looking fresh throughout the day. Many users report minimal need for touch-ups. The reformulated version even boasts up to 24-hour oil control and 12-hour stay-true color.
 * Matte Finish: If you prefer a matte finish, this powder is a winner. It effectively minimizes shine and creates a smooth, velvety look. The new formulation offers a "blurred-matte" finish, which aims to look more natural and less flat.
 * Convenient Packaging: The compact includes a mirror and a separate compartment for the sponge, making it ideal for on-the-go touch-ups.
Things to consider:
 * Potential for Dryness: Due to its matte finish and oil-absorbing properties, Studio Fix can sometimes cling to dry patches or feel a bit drying on already dry skin. Proper moisturization beforehand is key.

faceoff_negative.comments:
I discovered this powder by fluke during my trip to Ulta yesterday.  Was actually going in to try and snag one of the last original formula powders I could before 2.0 came out.  Unfortunately, I was too little, too late.  

Since this was already on the shelves, though, I figured I'd give it a try.  I really did try to have an open mind about it, despite being a loyal user of the previous studio fix.  But after using it for a day, all I can say is "nope, nope, nope."  

I'm not overstating when I say that this formula is nothing, I repeat NOTHING like the original.  In every sense of the word.  For starters, the shades are way WAY off compared to the previous version (I'm an NC25 in that formula and an N5 in the new one.).  It took trying 10 different shades to finally arrive at a close match in the new formula.  And that still isn't as close to my skin tone as the old NC25.  

To add insult to injury, Mac did two things to this new formula that fans of the original (myself included) begged/pleaded/implored them not to do: they removed talc and added mica.  

Now, I can't speak for others, but as a 43 year old woman, I simply CAN'T do mica.  It makes me look shiny, greasy, and just all around made up.  My personal goal when wearing makeup is to look as natural as possible.  The old formula delivered on that and then some.  This new mica-infused one, not so much.

On top of all of this, the powder looks incredibly thick and cakey when first applied.  (This means that touchups are simply out of the question.). The previous formula allowed multiple touchups/reapplications throughout the day without EVER looking cakey.  And believe me, I tested that limit - on multiple occasions.  

As for the final nail in the coffin (at least for me) with this powder‚Ä¶it has, in the course of a single day of use, started breaking me out.  I never EVER had that issue with the previous formula so it's obviously an ingredient in 2.0 that's causing it.  

This, along with everything else mentioned above, has pushed me away from Studio Fix, and by extension, from Mac as a whole.  Newer isn't always better and Mac has now made that mistake not once, but twice, with two of their most popular and beloved studio fix products.  This was, of course, despite numerous requests from their customers to leave them as is (if it ain't broke, don't fix it!!). If Mac wants to ignore and abandon their loyal customers in this manner, don't be surprised when those customers then abandon you for your competitors.  I know that's what I'll be doing.  Disappointed in you, Mac - yet again.
faceoff_negative.headline: Buyer beware -  it's nothing close to the original
